Package project4

Class MDeque<E>

Object
MDeque<E>
Type Parameters:
E - the type of elements held in this mdeque
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<E>
public class MDeque<E> extends Object implements Iterable<E>
A linear collection that supports element insertion and removal at three points: front, middle and back. The name mdeque is short for "double ended queue" (deque) with m for "middle" and is pronounced "em-deck". MDeque has no fixed limits on the number of elements it contains.

The remove operations all return null values if the mdeque is empty. The structure does not allow null as an element.

All pop..., push..., and peek... operations (from all three points of access) are constant time operations.

The middle position is defines as (size+1)/2. For mdeques with odd sizes, this is the actual middle element. For the mdeques with even sizes, this is the element, one past the middle of the elements. The position count is zero based. 

 [A, B, C, D]  -- middle element is C.
 [A, B, C, D, E] -- middle element is C.
